messages.content: is angular frequency and angular velocity the same

Angular frequency and angular velocity are often confused, yet angular frequency (usually denoted by \( \omega \)) refers to the rate at which an object rotates, measured in radians per second. Angular velocity, however, indicates the same quantity but provides direction, typically illustrated as a vector.
